<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Embassy in Korea</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v07p2</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d166</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">166</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-11-23T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW (Peace)/11–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-23T19:00:00-05:00">November 23, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>984. For Ambassador.<note n="1" xml:id="d166fn1">John J. Muccio.</note> For ur
                    conf info, current thinking in <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> is that all
                    nations which declared war or state of belligerency against Jap shld be party to
                    Jap peace treaty. It is envisaged 13 <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss>
                    countries wld be actual negotiating powers, with remaining 38 nations to
                    participate in consultative capacity.</p>
                <p>Present draft makes no provision for inclusion <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> in either category.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> wld appreciate ur views urgently as to
                    whether and to what extent provision shld be made for Korean participation in
                    Jap treaty, in terms both of domestic political considerations and of probable
                    substantive effect on negotiation of peace settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
